<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="577" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1590,1995]" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,1729,1752]" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species (
<figureCitation box="[526,624,1729,1752]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1859,1881]" captionTargetBox="[187,1380,198,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[187,1381,191,1832]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Polia ssp. adults. 1. P. hofer sp. n., male, holotype, China, N. Sichuan (GBG / ZSM); 2. P. h o f e r sp. n., male, paratype, China, N. Sichuan (GBG / ZSM); 3. P. h o f e r sp. n., female, paratype, China, N. Sichuan (OPB); 4. P. h o f e r sp. n., female, paratype, China, N. Sichuan (GBG / ZSM); 5. P. c o s t ir u f a, male, China, W. Sichuan, Batang (AFM); 6. P. c o s t ir u f a, male, China, W. Sichuan, Batang (OPB); 7. P. c o s ti r u f a, female, holotype, China Batang [Tibet], W. Sichuan (ZFMK); 8. P. costirufa, female, China, W. Sichuan, Litang (AFM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258180/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">
Figs 
<number box="[583,624,1729,1752]" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
</figureCitation>
) can be separated from the closely related 
<taxonomicName box="[1108,1233,1728,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costirufa">
<emphasis box="[1108,1233,1728,1752]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">P. costirufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1250,1348,1729,1752]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1859,1881]" captionTargetBox="[187,1380,198,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[187,1381,191,1832]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Polia ssp. adults. 1. P. hofer sp. n., male, holotype, China, N. Sichuan (GBG / ZSM); 2. P. h o f e r sp. n., male, paratype, China, N. Sichuan (GBG / ZSM); 3. P. h o f e r sp. n., female, paratype, China, N. Sichuan (OPB); 4. P. h o f e r sp. n., female, paratype, China, N. Sichuan (GBG / ZSM); 5. P. c o s t ir u f a, male, China, W. Sichuan, Batang (AFM); 6. P. c o s t ir u f a, male, China, W. Sichuan, Batang (OPB); 7. P. c o s ti r u f a, female, holotype, China Batang [Tibet], W. Sichuan (ZFMK); 8. P. costirufa, female, China, W. Sichuan, Litang (AFM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258180/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">
Figs 
<number box="[1308,1348,1729,1752]" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5–8</number>
</figureCitation>
) by it’s somewhat smaller size (wingspan 
<quantity box="[537,654,1764,1787]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.55" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="4.3" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" unit="mm" value="45.5" valueMax="48.0" valueMin="43.0">43-48 mm</quantity>
, those of 
<taxonomicName box="[772,899,1763,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costirufa">
<emphasis box="[772,899,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">P. costirufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<quantity box="[910,1027,1764,1787]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.6" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" unit="mm" value="48.0" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="46.0">46-50 mm</quantity>
) and lighter, more greyish forewing colouration without the reddish-brown tint characteristic of 
<taxonomicName box="[795,917,1797,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costirufa">
<emphasis box="[795,917,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">P. costirufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The reniform stigma on 
<taxonomicName box="[1194,1276,1797,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hofer">
<emphasis box="[1194,1276,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">P. hofer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is less whitish and distinct and 
<taxonomicName box="[333,456,1832,1856]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costirufa">
<emphasis box="[333,456,1832,1856]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">P. costirufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a remarkable, light creamy costal band on the upper half of the forewings. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[283,367,1867,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hofer">
<emphasis box="[283,367,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">P. hofer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[384,497,1868,1891]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1832,1854]" captionTargetBox="[293,1302,195,1805]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1315,191,1811]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 12. Polia ssp. male genitalia. 9. P. hofer sp. n., male, holotype, China, N. Sichuan, prep. OP 3246 m, (GBG / ZSM); 10. P. hofer sp. n., male, paratype, China, N. Sichuan, prep. GB 8690 m, (GBG / ZSM); 11. P. costirufa, male, China, W. Sichuan, prep. OP 3244 m (OPB); 12. P. costirufa, male, China, W. Sichuan, prep. GB 8703 m (GBG / ZSM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258182/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
) differs in the shorter uncus, the shorter but broader harpe, the narrower coecum, the broader carinal bar on the ventral side and the configuration and the shape of the vesica, complimented with a long medial diverticulum tipped with a cornutus. The female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[867,984,1937,1960]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1099,1121]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,200,1071]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1078]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Polia ssp. female genitalia. 13. P. h o f e r sp. n., female, paratype, China, N. Sichuan, prep. OP 3247 f, (OPB); 14. P. hofer sp. n., female, paratype, China, N. Sichuan, prep. GB 8687 f, (GBG / ZSM); 15. P. h o f e r sp. n., female, paratype, China, N. Sichuan, prep. GB 8689 f, (GBG / ZSM); 16. P. costirufa, female, holotype, China Batang [Tibet], W. Sichuan, GB 4497 f, (ZFMK); 17. P. c o s ti r u f a, female, China, W. Sichuan, Shaluli Shan, OP 3245 f, (OPB); 18. P. costirufa, female, China, W. Sichuan, Litang, GB 8705 f, (GBG / ZSM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258183/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">
Figs 
<number box="[922,984,1937,1960]" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" value="14.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="13.0">13-15</number>
</figureCitation>
) differs in the configuration of the cervix bursae with smaller sclerotisation.
